The paper deals with the problem of automated view planning for aerial imagery reconstruction, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and 3D reconstruction. The use of small aerial vehicles also suggests a robotics (RO) component. The paper also discusses the efficiency/quality trade-off, which is a common theme in graphics (GR) and computational geometry (CG). Finally, the use of algorithms for view selection and optimization suggests an artificial intelligence (AI) component.
